    "The accuracy and effectiveness of EWSs depend not just on the quality of data gathered from sensors, process understanding, and the ability to predict hazards accurately and assess their potential impact, but also the speed and effectiveness of communication, and the ability to make timely and effective decisions, e.g.",
    "implemented as Anticipatory Action in the humanitarian domain 14.. All of this requires preparedness to enable the EWS to be sustainable, effective, and enable the end users to take early actions to enhance their safety and reduce economic and social losses.",
    "An important aspect for EWS is the relevant time-scale.",
